Definition:
	A class is a data-type used as a blueprint for an object.

Syntax:
	class ClassName {

	};			<-- NB: Remember to put the semi-colon here.

Examples:
	class Student {
		public:
			std::string get_name();
			int get_age();
			char get_sex();

			void set_name( std::string new_name );
			void set_age( int new_age );
			void set_sex( char new_sex );

		private:
			std::string name;
			int age;
			char sex;
	};
